[
    {
        "text": "Rama and Lakshmana soon reached Rishyamukha.",
        "start": 9.16,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "It was a hilly region,",
        "start": 13.4,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "where many vanaras lived.",
        "start": 15.04,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Sugreeva was their leader.",
        "start": 17.24,
        "duration": 2.02
    },
    {
        "text": "He had the assistance  and friendship of Hanuman",
        "start": 20.02,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "a valiant and highly intelligent vanara.",
        "start": 23.72,
        "duration": 3.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman introduced himself to the two brothers",
        "start": 30.68,
        "duration": 3.56
    },
    {
        "text": "as the Minister  of the Vanara king Sugreeva.",
        "start": 34.58,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "He enquired about who Rama and Lakshmana were,",
        "start": 40.82,
        "duration": 3.5
    },
    {
        "text": "and what they were doing in the forest.",
        "start": 45.04,
        "duration": 2.06
    },
    {
        "text": "Rama told Hanuman about Ayodhya",
        "start": 50.42,
        "duration": 2.9
    },
    {
        "text": "his exile and abduction of Sita.",
        "start": 53.88,
        "duration": 3.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman took Rama and Lakshmana to Sugreeva.",
        "start": 60.98,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "They told their story to him.",
        "start": 79.3,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "Sugreeva made an offer to Rama,",
        "start": 103.98,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "that if Rama were to help him",
        "start": 107.04,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "to get rid of Vaali.",
        "start": 109.22,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "Then Sugreeva would summon the entire monkey,",
        "start": 111.18,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "and bear clan to help Rama find Sita.",
        "start": 114.6,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Rama seeing that,",
        "start": 121.58,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "injustice was done to Sugreeva",
        "start": 123.0,
        "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
        "text": "by Vaali, agreed.",
        "start": 125.2,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "In a fierce duel between Vaali and Sugreeva",
        "start": 202.36,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Rama shot dead Vaali with his arrow",
        "start": 206.14,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Sugreeva took over the reins of Kishkintha.",
        "start": 232.24,
        "duration": 3.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Thus, with the help of the entire vanara clan,",
        "start": 235.98,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "the search for Sita began...",
        "start": 240.44,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Fierce vanara warriors went North,",
        "start": 243.58,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "south, East and West",
        "start": 246.62,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "The troops that went south were led by the trusted Hanuman.",
        "start": 268.84,
        "duration": 4.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Searching thoroughly and unable to find Sita,",
        "start": 294.76,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "they finally reached the sea shore.",
        "start": 298.34,
        "duration": 2.06
    },
    {
        "text": "They wondered where to look for her now...",
        "start": 310.06,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "Jatayu's brother, the aged Sampathy,",
        "start": 319.78,
        "duration": 3.1
    },
    {
        "text": "also came to hear of the whole story,",
        "start": 323.04,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "through the vanaras.",
        "start": 325.72,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "He felt sad that Jatayu",
        "start": 327.48,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "had been killed by Ravana.",
        "start": 329.64,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Although, he could not fly,",
        "start": 334.82,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "he still had the sharp sight of a vulture.",
        "start": 337.18,
        "duration": 2.54
    },
    {
        "text": "He could see into the distance.",
        "start": 340.48,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "And he was the one to see Sita far across the ocean,",
        "start": 342.94,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "all alone and sad in the island of Lanka.",
        "start": 347.48,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "The vanaras felt happy",
        "start": 355.52,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "that atleast they knew where Sita was,",
        "start": 357.58,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "but they wondered,",
        "start": 361.54,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "how they could cross the vast ocean and reach Lanka.",
        "start": 362.96,
        "duration": 3.46
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman prayed to Rama",
        "start": 378.04,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Soon Hanuman was growing in size",
        "start": 380.82,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "and became so big",
        "start": 383.64,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "that the hills turned into tiny stones",
        "start": 385.22,
        "duration": 2.68
    },
    {
        "text": "under his feet.",
        "start": 387.9,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, thinking of his mission to find Sita,",
        "start": 390.16,
        "duration": 2.82
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman pressed his foot",
        "start": 393.42,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "hard into the ground",
        "start": 395.06,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "and leaped high into the air",
        "start": 396.94,
        "duration": 1.96
    },
    {
        "text": "he was soon flying over the ocean.",
        "start": 399.62,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "Finally, he landed",
        "start": 414.7,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "on the glistening shores of Lanka.",
        "start": 416.28,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "Once in Lanka, he set out to find Sita",
        "start": 423.46,
        "duration": 4.06
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman entered the Ashoka garden",
        "start": 431.54,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Beneath one of the trees",
        "start": 434.88,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "was the most beautiful woman",
        "start": 436.52,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman had ever seen",
        "start": 438.5,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "she was Sita.",
        "start": 440.8,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Sita was surrounded by many she demons.",
        "start": 442.82,
        "duration": 3.14
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuma waited for all the demons to sleep,",
        "start": 449.52,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "As he approached Sita.",
        "start": 452.56,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "Sita's heart was filled with gladness",
        "start": 462.26,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "as he presented her with Rama's ring",
        "start": 465.24,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "and told her that he was the messenger of Rama.",
        "start": 468.26,
        "duration": 3.56
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman narrated the entire story",
        "start": 476.34,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "of how Rama met Sugreeva",
        "start": 478.94,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "and their search for Sita.",
        "start": 481.52,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Sita gave hanuman a jewel that she wore,",
        "start": 484.74,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "which Rama would recognize,",
        "start": 487.84,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "She blessed Hanuman as he prepared to leave.",
        "start": 490.52,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Suddenly the demons awoke",
        "start": 495.94,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "When Ravana heard about the destruction",
        "start": 498.86,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "caused by a monkey",
        "start": 501.38,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "he sent his son Indrajit",
        "start": 503.08,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "to capture the monkey.",
        "start": 505.1,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "Indrajit was a very skilled warrior,",
        "start": 507.28,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "He used one of his  powerful weapons on Hanuman",
        "start": 516.84,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "imprisoned him and dragged him to Ravana's court.",
        "start": 523.96,
        "duration": 3.88
    },
    {
        "text": "When Hanuman was brought before the king",
        "start": 529.58,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "he was very impressed with the ten headed Ravana.",
        "start": 532.28,
        "duration": 3.22
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman then warned Ravana",
        "start": 536.1,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "about the danger he would be facing",
        "start": 538.44,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "if he did not return Sita to Rama",
        "start": 541.4,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "and asked for forgiveness.",
        "start": 544.38,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "Ravana became wild with rage",
        "start": 546.9,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "He ordered that Hanuman should",
        "start": 550.1,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "be put to death at once.",
        "start": 551.96,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "But, Vibheeshana his younger brother intervened",
        "start": 554.56,
        "duration": 3.1
    },
    {
        "text": "and pointed out",
        "start": 558.08,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "that it would be improper to kill a messenger.",
        "start": 559.66,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, Ravana ordered Hanuman's tail",
        "start": 563.88,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "to be set on fire",
        "start": 566.68,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "The king's men wrapped",
        "start": 568.58,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman's tail in cloth and set fire to it.",
        "start": 570.3,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "With his long tail on fire",
        "start": 577.7,
        "duration": 2.02
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman flew into the sky",
        "start": 579.9,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "He decided to set the city of Lanka ablaze",
        "start": 584.56,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "to punish Ravana.",
        "start": 588.24,
        "duration": 1.24
    },
    {
        "text": "He flew low over the city,",
        "start": 590.2,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "and set each building, palace and garden on fire",
        "start": 592.64,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "flames shot high into the sky",
        "start": 597.24,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "Then he finally jumped into the ocean",
        "start": 600.48,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "to put off the fire on his tail.",
        "start": 603.2,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman reached Kishkintha",
        "start": 626.04,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "and told Rama all about Sita's safety.",
        "start": 628.14,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Rama was overjoyed,",
        "start": 639.14,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "when he saw the jewel that,",
        "start": 641.02,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Hanuman had brought back.",
        "start": 642.6,
        "duration": 1.68
    }
]